    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomy of ' Euconnus complex'. Part XIII. Status of Afrotropical subgenera of Euconnus: Cephaloconnus, Cerviconnus, Ursoconnus and Nodoconnus (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Scydmaeninae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844809>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844821>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844823>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844825> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844809>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 8. Dorsal habitus (1 – 4) and set of labels of lectotypes (5, 7 – 8) and a holotype (6) of Euconnus (Cephaloconnus) hypertrophicus Franz (1, 5), Euconnus (Cerviconnus) bundukii Franz (2, 6), Euconnus (Ursoconnus) basilewskyi Franz (3, 7), and Euconnus (Nodoconnus) gomyanus Franz (4, 8)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/844809/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844821>
    dc:description "FIGURES 23 – 24. Morphological structures of Euconnus (Nodoconnus) gomyanus Franz. Head, prothorax and elytral base in dorsal view (23); head and prothorax in ventral view (24). Abbreviations: abp, antebasal pronotal pit; bst, basisternal part of prosternum; fr, frons; gp, gular plate; hr, hypostomal ridge; hyr, hypomeral ridge; mn, mentum; nss, notosternal suture; pcr, procoxal rest; ptp, posterior tentorial pit; smn, submentum; vt, vertex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/844821/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844823>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25 – 26. Morphological structures of Euconnus (Nodoconnus) gomyanus Franz. Left antenna of male in ventral view (25); pterothorax in ventral view (26). Abbreviations: msvp, mesoventral intercoxal process; mtvp, metaventral intercoxal process; pcr, procoxal rest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/844823/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.844825>
    dc:description "FIGURES 27 – 34. Aedeagus in ventral (27, 29, 31, 33) and lateral (28, 30, 32, 34) view. Euconnus (Cephaloconnus) hypertrophicus Franz (27 – 28); Euconnus (Cerviconnus) bundukii Franz (29 – 30); Euconnus (Ursoconnus) basilewskyi Franz (31 – 32); Euconnus (Nodoconnus) gomyanus Franz (33 – 34)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/844825/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

